6.  Technical Scope Definitions:

    This section defines key technical terms used throughout this document.

    - Backend System:

        Server-side services responsible for APIs, business logic, and data
        processing.

    - Distributed Processing:

        Workloads executed across multiple workers, threads, or services to improve
        throughput and reliability.

    - Worker Pipeline:

        Background job architecture used for CPU or I/O intensive processing such
        as media transformation.

    - Integration Layer:

        Abstraction layer responsible for communication with third-party APIs and
        external services.

    - Automation Tooling:

        CLI or programmatic utilities used to streamline operational or developer
        workflows.

